criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Aged 18-85;

          2. Patients receiving laparoscopic cholecystectomy due to benign gallbladder diseases;

          3. Older patient or accompanied by cardiopulmonary diseases (age>60 years, hypertension,
             Diabetes Mellitus, coronary heart disease, arrhythmia, chronic bronchitis, emphysema,
             history of heart surgery, history of lung surgery, history of mediastinal surgery,
             asthma, et al);

          4. Aged older than 60, with or without the above diseases;

          5. American society of Aneshesiologists (ASA) II or higher;

          6. Informed consent acquired.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Having contraindication of laparoscopic operations;

          2. History at epigastric surgery. -
